<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-17T11:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-17T11:36:00-05:00" n="890" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/7044</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Leavell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-17T10:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 18, 5.15
                                a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your July 6, 7 p.m. Have just been informed by Under Secretary of Foreign
                            Relations, the President and the Foreign Minister both being sick, there
                            are no restrictions imposed upon armed American vessels upon entrance
                            into any Guatemalan port.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LWH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>